{
  "texts": [
    "DurabilityThe two figures (Figs.",
    "19,20) illustrate the average effects of various SCMs on water absorption and chloride penetration respectively, based on the literature reviewed in this paper in Sect. 4.",
    "For water absorption, SF at a 10% replacement ratio shows the most significant reduction, achieving a decrease of approximately 60%, which highlights its effectiveness in minimizing water intake.",
    "EGP at a 15% replacement ratio and POFA at a 25% replacement level also demonstrate notable reductions, while RHA at 10% and MK at 15% result in moderate decreases.",
    "GGBFS at a 30% replacement level provides a smaller yet still significant reduction in water absorption."
  ]
}